Digital Telecom Rises Most in Six Years on Sale Speculation

-- B y   I a n   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-03-28T05:50:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/digital-telecom-rises-most-in-six-years-on-sale-speculation-1-.html
Digital Telecommunications
Philippines Inc. shares rose the most in more than six years in
Manila trading on speculation parent  JG Summit Holdings Inc. (JGS)  is
in talks to sell the venture to  Philippine Long Distance
Telephone Co. (TEL)   Digitel, as the phone company is known, surged 18 percent
to 1.83 pesos at the noon close of trading in Manila, the
sharpest gain since October 2004, while JG Summit gained 8.2
percent to 24.50 pesos, the highest since Dec. 8. Shares of
Philippine Long Distance, the nation’s biggest phone company,
gained 0.6 percent to 2,036 pesos.  “The speculation that JG Summit will sell Digitel wouldn’t
let up,” said Astro del Castillo, managing director at Manila-
based advisory firm First Grade Holdings Inc. “The story
spreading now is Philippine Long Distance has made an offer and
the entry of a new investor into Digitel is imminent.”  Philippine Long Distance Chairman Manuel Pangilinan
wouldn’t comment when asked by reporters in  Manila  today whether
the company will make an offer to buy Digitel. JG Summit Senior
Vice-President Bach Johann Sebastian, who said on March 23 that
there have been “expressions of interest” in Digitel, couldn’t
be reached on his mobile phone and didn’t respond to a text
message seeking comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
